<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="ida8727531-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5" identifier="/us/usc/t10/s1074c"><num value="1074c">§ 1074c.</num><heading> Medical care: authority to provide a wig</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A person entitled to medical care under this chapter who has alopecia resulting from the treatment of a malignant disease may be furnished a wig if the person has not previously been furnished one at the expense of the United States.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="ida8727532-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/98/525/tXIV/s1401/e/2/A">Pub. L. 98–525, title XIV, § 1401(e)(2)(A)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2616">98 Stat. 2616</ref>, § 1074b; renumbered § 1074c, <ref href="/us/pl/102/190/dA/tVI/s640/a/1">Pub. L. 102–190, div. A, title VI, § 640(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1991-12-05">Dec. 5, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/1385">105 Stat. 1385</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
